section.section:
The provisions of paragraph (1) of this subsection apply to a burn injury:
Causing 2nd or 3rd degree burns to 5 percent or more of the patient's body;
To the upper respiratory tract or laryngeal edema caused by inhaling super-heated air;
Which causes death; or
Which is likely to cause death.

text.section:
Notice under this section shall include:
The name and address of the patient, if known;
A description of the burn injury;
The reported cause of the burn injury, if given;
The patient's prognosis; and
Any other fact concerning the burn injury which might assist in detecting arson.
